# Git: no push by default

This workspace is **not** the Struxa CMS release pipeline. Work here is **plugins and themes** (and local integration). The upstream Struxa repo and its update story stay separate.

**Do not** run `git push` (to `origin` or any remote), open PRs, or publish branches **unless the user explicitly asks** in that conversation.

Local `git commit` is only when the user asks for commits; default is **no** push even after a commit.

If the user needs changes on a remote, they will say so (e.g. “push to my fork”, “open a PR”). Otherwise assume **all work stays local**.
